# Dockerfile-specific ignore for the tempo-compat driver build context.
#
# BuildKit picks `<dockerfile>.dockerignore` over the repo-root
# `.dockerignore` when both exist for the same Dockerfile. The root
# `.dockerignore` excludes `compatibility/` (because Dockerfile.local
# builds the cerberus binary and doesn't need it), but the tempo-compat
# driver lives under `compatibility/tempo/driver/` and DOES need its
# own source visible in the build context. This file narrows the
# exclusions accordingly.
#
# Pattern: mirror the root .dockerignore exclusions for everything
# unrelated to this driver, but DO NOT re-exclude `compatibility/` (so
# the `COPY . .` in the Dockerfile picks up the driver sources).

.git
.github
.claude
.envrc
.golangci.yml
.gremlins.yaml
.goreleaser.yml
.markdownlint.yaml
.markdownlintignore
.editorconfig
.commitlintrc.json
lefthook.yml

# Build outputs
bin/
dist/
coverage.out
coverage.html

# Editor / IDE
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp

# Test artifacts
test/e2e/playwright/node_modules/
test/e2e/playwright/test-results/
test/e2e/playwright/playwright-report/

# Documentation / contributor surface — never affects the driver build.
docs/
*.md
LICENSE

# Compose / k8s — not relevant to the driver compile.
docker-compose.yml
test/e2e/k3s/
test/e2e/grafana/

# Narrow the compatibility/ exclusion: keep compatibility/tempo/driver/
# in the build context (needed for `go build`), but skip the heavy
# upstream/ vendor + sibling harnesses to keep the image small.
compatibility/prometheus/
compatibility/loki/
compatibility/tempo/upstream/
compatibility/tempo/reports/
compatibility/tempo/scripts/
